  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "index": 1,
    "text": "GRADUATION PROJECT REPORT",
    "style": "None"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "index": 2,
    "text": "Emotion Recognition & Face Recognition Module",
    "style": "None"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "index": 4,
    "text": "Part of: Assistive Vision System for Visually Impaired Users",
    "style": "None"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "index": 8,
    "text": "1. Project Overview",
    "style": "Heading 1"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "index": 9,
    "text": "This report documents the design, implementation, and evaluation of two AI modules for the Assistive Vision System — a graduation project aimed at helping visually impaired users understand their social environment through real-time audio feedback.",
    "style": "None"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "index": 11,
    "text": "The system uses a camera to detect and recognize faces, analyze emotional states, and announce results via Text-to-Speech. Voice commands allow full interaction without keyboard or screen.",
    "style": "None"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "index": 13,
    "text": "1.1 Modules in This Report",
    "style": "Heading 2"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "index": 15,
    "text": "1.2 System Objectives",
    "style": "Heading 2"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "index": 16,
    "text": "Detect and recognize faces in real time using deep learning.",
    "style": "List Paragraph"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "index": 17,
    "text": "Classify facial emotions from a CNN model trained on FER-2013 dataset.",
    "style": "List Paragraph"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "index": 18,
    "text": "Provide audio feedback to visually impaired users via Text-to-Speech.",
    "style": "List Paragraph"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "index": 19,
    "text": "Support offline operation using local Vosk speech recognition.",
    "style": "List Paragraph"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "index": 20,
    "text": "Deploy on Raspberry Pi 4 Model B for portable, wearable use.",
    "style": "List Paragraph"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "index": 23,
    "text": "2. System Architecture",
    "style": "Heading 1"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "index": 24,
    "text": "Both modules work under a unified Logic Controller. The decision pipeline for each detected face is shown below:",
    "style": "None"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "index": 27,
    "text": "Figure 1: System Logic Flow — Decision pipeline for each detected face",
    "style": "None"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "index": 29,
    "text": "2.1 Shared Components",
    "style": "Heading 2"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "index": 32,
    "text": "3. Emotion Recognition Module",
    "style": "Heading 1"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "index": 33,
    "text": "The Emotion Recognition module detects faces and classifies facial expressions into one of seven emotion categories in real time, providing the primary sensing capability for the assistive system.",
    "style": "None"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "index": 35,
    "text": "3.1 Processing Pipeline",
    "style": "Heading 2"
  },
  {
