    "style": "Heading 2"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "index": 69,
    "text": "4. Face Recognition Module",
    "style": "Heading 1"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "index": 70,
    "text": "The Face Recognition module identifies known individuals from a local database, detects blocked persons silently, and supports fully voice-controlled person management.",
    "style": "None"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "index": 72,
    "text": "4.1 Processing Pipeline",
    "style": "Heading 2"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "index": 74,
    "text": "Figure 7: Face Recognition Pipeline — Complete processing flow",
    "style": "None"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "index": 76,
    "text": "4.2 Model Selection — Facenet512",
    "style": "Heading 2"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "index": 78,
    "text": "Figure 8: Face Recognition Models — LFW Benchmark Comparison",
    "style": "None"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "index": 80,
    "text": "Facenet512 was selected for its highest accuracy (99.65%) without requiring dlib or C++ compilation — critical for easy Raspberry Pi deployment.",
    "style": "None"
  },
  {
